```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "scheduler": "SLURM",
    "job_name": "slepc@3.16.0-cmplx",
    "account": "use300",
    "reservation": "rocky8u7_testing",
    "partition": "ind-shared",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 16,
    "memory": "32G",
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "output_file": "%x.o%j.%N",
    "scratch_directory": "/scratch/${USER}/job_${SLURM_JOB_ID}",
    "system_name": "expanse",
    "spack_version": "0.17.3",
    "spack_instance": {
      "name": "cpu",
      "version": "b",
      "directory": "/cm/shared/apps/spack/${SPACK_VERSION}/${SPACK_INSTANCE_NAME}/${SPACK_INSTANCE_VERSION}"
    },
    "intel_license_file": "40000@elprado.sdsc.edu:40200@elprado.sdsc.edu",
    "spack_package": "slepc@3.16.0",
    "spack_compiler": "intel@19.1.3.304",
    "spack_variants": "~arpack ~blopex ~cuda ~rocm",
    "spack_dependencies": "^petsc@3.16.1/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' petsc@3.16.1 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ~mpi +complex)",
    "spack_spec": "${SPACK_PACKAGE} % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ${SPACK_VARIANTS} ${SPACK_DEPENDENCIES}"
  }
}
```

This script utilizes SLURM (Simple Linux Utility for Resource Management) for resource management and scheduling. The script runs on a system called "expanse" using the "rocky8u7_testing" reservation on the "ind-shared" partition. It requests 1 node with 1 task per node, 16 CPUs per task, 32GB of memory, and a runtime of 30 minutes. 

The script also uses `spack`, a package manager for scientific software, to install the SLEPc package (version 3.16.0) compiled with the Intel compiler (version 19.1.3.304) and specific variants. SLEPc depends on the PETSc package (version 3.16.1), also installed using spack.
